Let $S(n)$ denote the number of sequences of length $n$ formed by the three
letters A, B, C with the restriction that the C's (if any) all occur in a
single block immediately following the first B (if any). For example ABCCAA,
AAABAA, and ABCCCC are counted in, but ACACCB and CAAAAA are not. Derive a
simple formula for $S(n)$ and use it to calculate $S(10)$.
